    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for the rename feature:\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary\n\n**4 files, 8 targeted edits, zero new files, zero new imports.**\n\n### How it works\nRename = copy the source manifest JSON → delete the source manifest JSON. Model weights (blobs) live in a shared content-addressed store and are never duplicated — only the tiny manifest pointer file moves.\n\n### Changes at a glance\n\n| File | What's added | Location |\n|---|---|---|\n| `api/types.go` | `RenameRequest{Source, Destination string}` | after `CopyRequest` (line 765) |\n| `api/client.go` | `Rename(ctx, *RenameRequest) error` using `POST /api/rename` | after `Copy()` (line 387) |\n| `server/routes.go` | `RenameHandler` method | after `CopyHandler` (line 1483) |\n| `server/routes.go` | `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` | after `/api/copy` route (line 1698) |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | `RenameHandler` function | after `CopyHandler` (line 1350) |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | `renameCmd` (`cobra.ExactArgs(2)`) | after `copyCmd` (line 2263) |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | `renameCmd` in env-docs loop | in the `for _, cmd := range` block (line 2298) |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | `renameCmd` in `rootCmd.AddCommand` | after `copyCmd` (line 2345) |\n\n### Handler error logic\n1. Parse/validate source → **400**  \n2. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` fails with `os.ErrNotExist` → **404**  \n3. Parse/validate destination → **400**  \n4. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` succeeds (already exists) → **409**  \n5. `CopyModel(src, dst)` errors → **500**  \n6. `srcManifest.Remove()` errors → **500**  \n7. All pass → **200**",
